caption: Once again, a great meal from Joti. Aloo Ghobi and saag paneer...so so yummy.  Take out was very fast and hot. Great family business.

From the first moment  you arrive in this place  they give you a great feeling. Very friendly hosts, it is a nice place to to go out with buddies or with your date. Excellent  cuisine, specialist  chief cook and stuff, competitive  cost and courteous  service. Highly recommended.
That is crazy This place is to over price for that good 17 dólares for 2 side rice e soup. Or supost be chicken Marsala no soup Never again
Chicken Korma
One of the very few Indian places around Greater Boston area with amazing north Indian flavour.
Some of the best food I’ve had in awhile, and the service was so fast! Everything tasted so fresh and homemade, I will definitely be ordering again. Thank you!
I constantly stop by grabbing some food here. I love the rapid service and well made food. Keep up the good work.
I've always ordered Indian food from Joti Palace to go, either pick-up or delivery, and it's been good. I've never eaten inside, so I can't comment on that.

Really good tasting food but horrendous customer service. We ordered through Uber Eats like any other time before, but this time we were missing food from our order. We called the restaurant and the guy on the phone was being rude to my wife and accused the Uber driver of taking the food even though the bags had zero evidence of being tampered with. The guy didn't even offer an alternative solution.

Been going here for over 10 years, owned by the same family. Really good and consistent food, great flavor and they can make anything as spicy as you want. I order vegetable samosas and garlic Nan with everything. Some of the apps are portioned like meals, always delicious.
Food was average. They make North Indian recipes better compared to South Indian. I did not like Biryani.

This family owned business makes the BEST indian food around! I eat plant based and they have a ton of vegetarian options that are all AMAZING! I wish I was one of their kids so I could eat this good every day! Highly recommend and BONUS, they serve alcohol now too!

This has to be by far the best indian food around. My girlfriend introduced me to this jem when I first visited Mass, and now that I live here, we have it as much as possible. The great folks that cook in the back are basically five star chefs and I would love to have one of their recipes... I'd ask about their alcohol option as well. KEEP UP THE GREAT WORK GUYS!!!!

I ordered delivery from Slice when I was at work. It said it would be an hour, standard for a second party delivery app. The food got to my work in half the time I was quoted and it was AMAZING! I got Chicken Tikka Masala, Garlic Naan and Vegetable Samosas. It was piping hot and some of the most delicious Indian food I have ever had (even hours later and cold). I will definitely order from here again!
Would surely recommend trying this spot. Excellent ambience, flavorful food, awesome customer service. Great work.
Try the tikka masala and the paneer options! Walk here from J Malden Center!

I ordered non-vegetarian thali like right now. Dal was very sour, like the worst ever. Even a cow can cook better. They apparently forgot to add gulab jamun and when called they replied we'll add it next time. Wow and claps for the customer service.
This restaurant is wonderful and broad, the meals was enchanting and the prices were very inexpensive. quick, efficient service and very amiable waiters. Highly recommended.

Ok.  I understand mistakes are made and I’m forgiving of an error the first time but when the same mistake happens to the same customer within 2 weeks, there is something wrong! REALLY WRONG!  Two weeks ago, I ordered the Chicken Tikka Masala.  After eating 3/4 of what was on my plate I bit into a staple. I found a total of 2 staples in either the rice or the sauce.  I called and complained and the manager politely replaced my order the following week.  I placed another order today and found a long strand of hair in the rice. I called the manager again and told him what happened and was told the problem was with me, not the food.  While I will no longer patronize this poor excuse of a restaurant, I would only suggest you thoroughly inspect your food before biting in!  Bon Apetit
Worst food
It took them over an hour to deliver my food and they are literally 5 minutes away from my place. The food was tasteless and the driver was rude. Bad experience

I eat there frequently i love the food the food is good.my only issue every time i go there i don't get good service from the woman i was there today my water glass was very low and she filled up everyone elses water and walked right past me twice she did she does not seem to be very friendly i never see her smile

I ordered the cocanut chicken Korma, the chicken was raw. The sauce was watery, and I couldn't taste anything but cocanut and sugar. I had to re-cook it myself again at home and add my own spices. It was a waste of money and big time.
good food! I'll re visit again! I wish they remodel the place.
Love the food! Staff is so friendly. It's my local go-to for Indian food.
Excellent food at a great price! Friendly, helpful staff. The owner stopped by our table and chatted a bit.
I prefer this place a lot. there is a friendly air. The cuisine is exeptionaly good. the service is effective and the waiters are polite. The price is fair. deeply recommend.

Big Indian food fan, I was initially skeptic due to some mixed reviews but I’m glad I decided to give it a shot anyways. The chicken Tikka Masala was very delicious, also tried the Chicken biryani, also very good. Will go again and would advice anyone to give it a try.
Authentic food

Don't understand all the negative reviews this place has generated. In my experience (and I eat A LOT of Indian food) this place offers GREAT quality DELICIOUS Indian food at very affordable prices !!! Lunch buffet selections are a little limited, true, but quality/taste is high !! At dinner time, EVERYTHING I've had has been delicious. Curries, Kormas, even Vindaloo (too spicy for my wuss-y palate, but still wonderfully tasty) all consistently earn very high marks !! The non-vegetarian appetizer is a meal in itself, with five different styles of meat (10 pieces total) all different, and each wonderful in its own way. And I've NEVER had a problem with the staff ... they've all been gracious and welcoming. This restaurant has been here for over 20 years, so they must be doing SOMETHING right !!! I am a big fan - ignore the haters and give them a try. You'll be glad you did!!!
Great food, friendly staff!

Horrible. A humongous waste of time. I'm not going to get the 1 hour back in my life. Such horrible service and the man who runs this resteraunt cant't even speak  nicely to the customers. The veg biryani wasn't made with basmati rice and the rice was oddly sweet and sticky The pakoras should not have been served to me, but to the farm pigs. Don’t go

Horrible. Horrible. Terrible. I got some food from there and everything there was disgusting. The best thing there was the water, and it was not even their water it was my own bottle. When I Ate the veg biryani I almost threw up. IT was sticky and gross and definitely not fresh. I almost told the owner to remake the biryani because it was horrible but I did not because the owner would get mad. Not ever coming back! Don’t go no matter what. I should have listened to my parents and the other 1000000000000000000000000000000 people who told me it was bad.
Pretty good food. Service was fairly quick and food was pretty tasty. It was a little untypical but for the most part good. Although the staff was a little rude

They use long grain white rice instead of basmati rice and the food is utterly bland. I’m confused as to how anyone enjoys such flavorless food. We ordered spicy and it had NO HEAT whatsoever. The chicken vindaloo was overly sour, the palak paneer lacked seasoning, and the chicken tikka masala tasted more like a tomato bisque. Perhaps they ran out of all their spices? Hands down, the worst Indian I’ve ever had.
Good food

Don't go to this place. Its a total money waste place. No quality, hygiene, and taste. They use the cheapest groceries and worst spices to cook food. I wish this restaurant gets inspected and penalized for selling stale food.

For anyone saying this is great Indian food. I don’t think you ever had Indian food. Their rice was not basmati rice and their chicken Marsala was DISGUSTING! I’m so disappointed. I’ll be staying with D’Guru. Now THAT is REAL Indian food!
I ordered a food today and this is going to be the last order. I am never going to order food again from this restaurant . Taste was just disgusting

Delicious home made Indian food. My family and I are glad to find this restaurant in our neighborhood. The restaurant owners have made menu accommodations to a vegan family member. We really appreciate the wonderful customer service. keep up with the great home made food and the excellent customer service!
Not bad.  I loved the Taj Mahal beer.
Yummy food. Best Indian in the neighborhood. A little slow. Good lunch buffet.

Another Biryani-Conning Indian restaurant in Boston area. They have no clue how to make biryani. The chicken pieces are thick and rubbery, the style of cooking is wrong - I should have known when they said 'nuts & raisins' in Biryani. Bas taste, too much oil and Not authentic at all !
I ordered food here, had such a bad experience!!!!!!!! Never ever go. Gulab Jamoon went bad. I request restuarant guys not to give spoiled stuff!

Lunch Buffet is light on items but what was there was fair to good:  curry goat, tandoori chicken, chicken masala, curried veggies, chutney, rice pudding.  Not bad.  The food probably sits there a little too long as traffic in the restaurant  seemed very light.

I can't believe that the reviews for Joti Palace are so low. It's one of our favorite Indian restaurants in the greater Boston area. The only Indian restaurant that is comparable is Punjab Palace in Brighton. We've never been to the actual restaurant, but we frequently get them through GrubHub. I would recommend Joti Palace to anyone who enjoys quality Indian food.

It was the worst biryani we’ve ever had. . I loved biryani and sheek kebab this is one of my favorite food. I tried to see if they make good beryani and to be honest I’m not gonna lie their  beryani sucks. Food sucks.! Nasty.! It was my first time ordering food in this restaurant through Uber eats and I will never order food from here.! I am so disappointed.

We are from Malaysia and have a great number of Indian community and enjoy Indian cuisine almost a few times in a week. I have to say the dishes made by Joti Palace were very close to what used to please our palates. Great atmosphere and plenty of dining space as the restaurant cater take out more than dine-in guests. The servant or waitress was very polite and patiently explain some of the menu that were less familiar to us. I recommend the sword fish tikka masala and fish pakora. They are superb to be taken with garlic naan and rice! I will return to the restaurant and try out different menu in the future.

You see and this why people why never had Indian food before eat here and say they don't like Indian food. Chicken Marsala was nasty, tastes like the just put all heavy cream and no tomato sauce. The chicken used was so dry. The Pakora was burnt.. tasted like it was fried in old oil. I will never eat here again.. worst Indian food I've ever had.
Authentic Indian food which will satisfy our taste buds
Food smells like a dead man.. don’t ever go it this restaurant!!

Due to some busy schedule we ordered Biryani in this restaurant and they just sent us the vegetable rice Biryani by mixing with boiled chicken. The rice was spoiled and smells like a someone dead.  We just trashed the food and had a instant wrap.  I think this is the worst restaurant I ever seen.
Best Indian food in New England!  Very rare to find one of these gems
Ok, you can go there for once.

Best Indian food in town! I typically come here for the buffets but can also highly recommend the Chicken Biryani. All their foods have a nice kick to it and it tastes great. Portions are very generous and the cost is very average.
The owner does not treat his employee well and comes across rude

The place doesn’t look so intriguing when you walk in but trust me don’t need be small minded and have a seat and enjoy the delicious food. My first time dining out at an Indian place and it was so delicious !

The food just doesn’t taste good. The pakoras were burnt to a crisp, and even the tap water they served us tasted like dish soap. The service is good, they even made me a vegetable mango curry they had the ingredients for but was not on the menu. The curry was passable but the ingredients definitely aren’t fresh.

Food is decent. I've ordered a few times since moving since my former favorite spots don't deliver to our new house. Delivery is consistently late. Any time I call to inquire they're rude and unconcerned that I expected food at a certain time. I've never eaten in the restaurant so can't speak to that service.

biriyani that I had , was a worst experience, pouring gravy and rice on a plate then they called that as a biriyani... only thing I like there is fountain soda 🥤 have unique taste like other place thanks for that
No parking available
Very delicious! I got the chicken mikhah and it was so flavorful. The vegetable samosa were so crunchy and yummy. Love this little place. So under appreciated.
The food isn't fresh and they got my order wrong

Visiting from DC. Five star food, atmosphere/decor less so, but great experience overall. Mixed grill - hot had so much flavor. Best Na'an EVER!!! OMG! Friendly owners, 18 years running. Talked with some locals who have been coming for over a decade. Samoas great too.

Joti Palace is amazing Indian at a reasonable price. It is consistently done right. Every customer is treated like a treasured family member. As a chef I respect good food, but I keep going back for great food. I have been a patron at Joti for 20 years!

Use caution before ordering from here. Plain and simple, if you want quality food, avoid this place. The food is inedible. We had ordered alo papdi chat, the papdi had the texture of cardboard. Stale and tasteless. The Malai kofta is worse than hospital food, I mean, no salt? No spice? For heaven's sake, this is an "Indian" restaurant.

DO NOT ORDER FOOD FROM HERE. It's a ripoff! First we ordered food using the prices online and when the delivery man came he told us the prices increased and the online prices are not right with no proof. The portions were small. If you can choose another Indian restaurant!
Food is ok. For the price, the ambience is underwhelming. Revamp the place!
You can never get fresh food here. Stock base sauces and some sautéed veggies and meat. They should close down this place. Health hazard.
I never recommend this hotel to anyone.
Excellent food, friendly and helpful staff, family owned and run.

If you've heard about how Mela is the best of Boston area then you've heard wrong. I personally loved the setup at Joti palace!! Sure it's not fancy as a restaurant but the food, oh yes you will love the food. It's got that north indian food taste that one will crave after not being in India for long time. If you are thinking to go on a date night in an upscale place then Joti palace is not for you but if you want to have upscale Indian food then yes this is the right place!!

This is a long time favorite for my husband and me! The quality of food is outstanding (especially considering the low prices). There's always been ample seating when we go because they do a very strong takeout/delivery service. The owners are fantastic people. Since we've moved, we don't go here as much, but they still always remember us and our order!
The food was amazing and was clean. Granted it's not a 5-star restaurant but if you're going for authentic Indian food, then this is the place to go!

Don't order any non veg chicken items using grub hub.. we had ordered from here in the evening from grub hub and the order they prepared was done using stale chicken.. we are now at the restaurant returning the food..  UPDATE.. when we reached there the manager was apologetic and he had the chef re-make our order properly.. the food was good.. not sure why the grubhub orders get screwed up though.. call and order they will make it properly:.

This place is a joke. I ordered my food on Foodler and they refuse to deliver just because I left a 15% tip for the driver. The guy called me saying that it is not worth it. Can you believe that? I had been there in person and the food was ok (nothing special) but the service was HORRIBLE. Never again!
Good service. Food was good but not great

Let me make clear on my review. I am a South Indian, so we generally have clarity between pulav and biryani.. These people made biryani using ingredients of both, so it tasted worst.. Beware who are expecting hyderabadi biryani, PEAS and CAPSICUM are part of these people biryani..  Appetizers, we ordered is non-veg platter hoping to taste best of everything.. every piece of meat tasted like freshly heated rubber.. if you are looking for good taste, this is not the place..

Wife likes their food... However, both time we ordered delivery we waited for a long time the last time we ordered we wait an hour and forty minutes. If you want to give them a shot go pick it up. I give them three stars because the food is not bad, but the delivery time it ridiculous.
Takeout meal: As always, our entrees were well-prepared, but the vegetable pakoras appetizer was burnt and inedible.  Can't believe they sent the order out of the kitchen that way! --Jbb
Dont try chicken biryani!!
Always want cash for quick pick ups no good with that Only samosas and malai kofta are good.

The food was ok. Average but it was tasty. The nan was plain but fresh and hot.  The food was NOT greasy, over cooked or under cooked, salty or burned... We had 3 appetizers, soups, 3 entrees and strong coffee. There was no food poisoning for the 5 of us or uncomfortable gases.  Service was good, so for the folks  who gave 1 star... I don't know what you were expecting, but I suspect you have unrealistic expectations or something personal happening here. If you can't give an objective review, stay home and cook if you can do better

Terrible..! Just order few types of naan breads! They were uncooked, extremely thick and flour like taste...Basically I wont say them naans at all but raw loafs??  A dinner party was spoilt due to these. Later on got stomach pain due to raw this food. Never again this place.

Third class food.Yesterday I had ordered a biryani and chicken tikka n I was like hmm what the hell is this???never seen a biryani with lots of onions and capsicum only no any dry fruits nothing else and chicken tikka it was horrible...it's like watery chicken uncooked n poor customer service.

worst food today. I ordered "Bhuna Lamb" and Lamb was completely undercooked . I called them to the take the remaining portion back , I got a very discouraging answer. This was worst customer service.
Food tastes really good!

I got sick and had to stay home from my family's Thanksgiving trip, but $25 worth of yummy Indian food is making me feel much better. The chicken korma is creamy and flavorful and everything korma should be, the rice is tender, the coconut soup is perfectly sweet, the masala tea is aromatic and warming, and the meat samosas were filling without being too heavy, although I wish they'd been a little spicier. The only thing I wasn't crazy about was the garlic naan, but that's just a personal preference; I don't like cilantro and didn't think to ask about it. The delivery was estimated to take about an hour to an hour and a half, and was pretty much exactly an hour, and the delivery person was polite and pleasant.  In short, very good food at a very reasonable price with reliable delivery service. I'm happy I ordered from them, and will definitely do so in the future. I do wish they offered peshwari naan, though!

I have been to Joti Palace several times. Its a nice place to dine with family/friends. The ambience is good. The staff is very helpful, polite and welcoming. Food is good. I especially like their chicken tikka masala, onion kulacha, garlic naan and Mango lassy. The taste is close to what you would get in India, not exactly same though. Dont forget to tell them "extra spicy" if you are an indian :)  Ambience : 5 stars Staff and service : 5 stars Food quality : 4 stars
the quality is about average at best but I still order it every month or so for its portion for the price till they cut the portion in literally half recently
I've been to India, this place is legit and amazing. the only thing that this place has that Indian food does is the food born illnesses.
Both the curries and the breads tasted horrible. It was as if they did a favor just by serving us food.

went there first time to pick up the food. this place horrible inside and out, from food to the staff. hated it. saw the staff was using microwave to warm the frozen food. on the top of that they over charge me when I submitted a coupon. they charged me extra 20% because of coupon. when I demand explanation she told me its for the carry out container. I never hard restaurant charge extra 20% for damn plastic container!! after over paying for the food when I came home I found out they didn't even give me all the item, which they mentioned in their menu under veg thali and non veg thali. I called them back with my complain but staff was very rude. they denied their mistake and because I asked owners name and number they hung up on me. so pls stay away from that place unless wanna get ripped and get worst food..
I hope that writing this will remind me not to order Shrimp Vindaloo. The worst shrimp vindaloo ever eaten.It looked like shrimps were frozen and might have been a year old.I also undercooked.

Got some take out here since its one of the only Indian places in the Malden Center area.  This place is always empty when I walk by which makes me wonder sometimes.  The service is fast and the food is typical indian fair but nothing exceptional.  I got the paneer korma dish and some samosas and overall its not bad but nothing great.  The portions are good sized for the price and you get rice with your entree.
(Translated by Google) worst briyani ever  (Original) worst briyani ever
Food was good but the order took almost 2 hours to arrive.
Best indian cuisines ever
N I C E..

The food is good but the service is terrible. I ordered from them about 6 months ago and it took forever to get my food because the driver said he got lost, so I gave them the benefit of the doubt. When I ordered from them a few months later, the same thing happened but instead of waiting an hour, it took 90 minutes. I only live about 2.5 miles a way...I should have just picked up my food but I didn't. When I called to find out the status of my order I was disconnected so I called back and the woman told me she'd call the driver. I told her to cancel my order and that I was coming down there to get my refund. I was again disconnected and received a phone call from the driver saying he couldn't find my house. When I tried to cancel my order, they wouldn't do it and only offered to take off the tip. I will never order from them again.

We took a thali and the food was extremely good.  The service was also very good.  We had some left overs and they insisted that they would wrap it for us.  We also tried pakoras and it was excellent. Overall very good.

This review is completely honest. I consider myself a foodie, and this place was terrible. We had a coupon for this place so stopped in to get some Indian food to go.  We waited for a while; the interior was very gross. It was empty.  Worst of all, the food was bad. The sauces were completely watered down, like they had been trying to skimp and save money and intentionally watered down our sauces.  This was summer of 2012, and we haven't been back since because it was definitely one of the worst restaurants I've ever eaten from. I would not go back for any reason.

Negatives: Not the best Portion size. When taking out, requesting delivery you really have to specify that you need "GREEN chutney" else you wont get it :-)  Positives: Delivery in Malden... I think there is a little extra charge (very nominal)... but for someone who doesnt want to drive and park. this is good. When everyone closes doors at you (10PM), this guy is ready to deliver and is prompt at delivering + He was patient for me to open the door for him. (Sorry brother)  Neutrals: Average Service at restaurant, Food Taste
some of the best Indian food around. great food, fast delivery. judge by the food, not the atmosphere ...
